it's been a hot & dry summer & running in 30C+ weather ain't easy! 

some things that have helped ease the heat for me:
• wear a hat x sunglasses - so simple - protects our bodies from overheating & protects against uv rays
• i wear my @adidasterrex run vest to carry water & electrolytes even on the short distances
• listen to a playlist called 'Vegas pool party' - trust me lol
• leave the egos at home - stop if the bod says stop, find shade, fuel up & then keep going

mondays are my saturdays when it comes to adulting content & i was in the grocery store around noon  squeezing the avocados & the song Big Bad Leroy Brown came on - an oldie, a classic. tbh grocery store playlists are usually everything we all need in the moment & i was singing under my breath as i walked the aisles between the bread & the beef opportunities. & then a sweet older lady with a hand crafted wooden cane met me at the lemons - she smiled & asked me to reach up & get her a bag as she was singing it too.. & then i moved on & a young man with the most beautiful tattoos holding the hand of his five year old son said excuse me as he grabbed a tub of hummus & he was singing it too.. & this was all just an opportunity to remember how art pulls us together no matter who we are or what our story is.. it's a connector when we feel so very far apart.. & to keep making your art too. 🎶 

photos are a throwback to a beautiful afternoon with @whitneyerinphotography in toronto's queen west.

social_posts.post_text:
big blue skies and little umbrellas. 

we're on the big island for our 🍯🌙. with the timing of us meeting in life, this is our first significant vacation together, which makes us giggle cause we've sort of taken the path less traveled (again..) but how cute. 

i've been lucky to have been here before & this is C's first experience - i get excited watching people get excited about the things that made my eyes glow when they were my firsts too. it's a slow life, a grateful life over here.. a sweet life with sweet ppl. & we kept it slow for the first few days - snorkeling, reading & a sunset spot every night.

i can't stop talking about how well i've slept lol (for someone that doesn't sleep well =) 

C can't stop talking to everyone lol getting to know the locals & asking permission to hear about their culture & moʻolelo aka stories. 🤙it's one of the things i love muchly about him - his passion for learning about how we're all different which makes us all the same & making others feel warm & understood.

more mo'olelo to come. 🌺
nature is my people. 🙃🌺

i ran a 10k in hawai'i. i'd like to run more races when i travel. 😎

i was bummed to be missing the @terryfoxhometownrun this year & the emcee said this Run for Hope was inspired by Terry's marathon of hope. love when things align. 

the oceanside track was incredible & the heat x hills were challenging. i didn't run my best time but placed my best. the runner's high took over. 

also nod to the vipers on their first race lol iykyk. 😎 & my hubby for his support.

2nd overall female
1st overall in age group 
shoes : adidas ultraboost light ///

grateful for this morning 🤙
@adidasrunning 
@adidas

the floor is lava but in real life. 

the big island has three (some say four) active volcanoes & while here, Kīlauea erupted. we hiked out to see it. i wore my volcano jacket lol. nature is so beautiful & so intimidating at the same time. jurassic park esque. definitely a once in a lifetime kind of moment. we're still wow-ing about the day.

let's be real - we barely got out of our bathing suits 😎
.. but when we did, loud colours and big prints were it. 🌺

beach -> drinks with friends -> dinner for two.
just for fun in hawaii.
🌴

it's the little things ... but they all add up. 

this is a saying that continues to hang out with me in life. i first heard it when I was on a work trip, oh i'd say back in maybe 2014. it was with Right to Play Canada & we were able to spend time with the community of Whitefish River First Nation in northern ontario. i had just finished an interview with Chief Shining Turtle & the cameras had turned off & left & it was just the two of us in this small, wooden hut that was soon to be refurbished into a dressing room for the outdoor rink. he told me he lived right behind the rink & that one of his favourite sounds while he stirs at home is hearing the puck hit the boards. to him this meant that there was a place for the children to be safe & that their minds in that moment were wrapped around their dreams. he also said he likes being at the rink when everyone is asleep & just staring at the stars. 

i said it's the little things, eh.. 
..& he said yes, but they all add up. 

..to be continued..

lucky 13. ///

checking off another week of training. i like to feel out my footing/test the waters/weather the cold lol before i announce the plan in everything i do in life but i'm bucketlisting in 2024 & i'm intimidated & excited & grateful. 

i called today's run 'lucky 13' cause i felt super in the pocket from the jump on my 13K in -13C (-19C). my body does NOT love the cold so it was super mental too. 

.. i've fallen in love with the process.
& if you've reached out about your run goals/training, i'm glad you did. i love cheering each other on. let's keep talkin'.
